<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0977B229ECC5FF4A251A4BA0" blockId="35.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ECC5FF4A21A94A99" bold="true" box="[199,418,150,176]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Short description:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229EDA9FF4B22C74A98" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[427,716,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuiformis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229EDA9FF4B22C74A98" box="[427,716,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Glossogobius tenuiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229EF7DFF4B23EF4A99" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[895,996,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229EF7DFF4B23EF4A99" box="[895,996,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">G. giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex and is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229E983FF4B20D34AFD" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229E983FF4B20D34AFD" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">G. giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2156C340977B229ECE3FF6721654AFC" box="[225,366,187,213]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
by each of the sensory papilla lines being composed of single rows (vs. 2–3 rows or more in several lines), the absence or very short (and often only a few papillae long) sensory papilla line 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229E8C7FF0224D84AD1" box="[1221,1235,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">6</emphasis>
(vs. row 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229E938FF0225434AD1" box="[1338,1352,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">6</emphasis>
always distinctly present and long); lower pre-dorsal scale counts (7–16 vs. 15–24) and gill rakers on outer face of first arch 1+1+9–11 usually 1+1+10 (vs. 1–2+1+6–9, usually 1–2+1+7–8). Dorsal-fin rays 
<collectionCode id="ED4395980977B229E863FEFB248A4B68" box="[1121,1153,295,321]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">VI</collectionCode>
, second dorsal-fin rays I, 9, anal-fin rays I, 8–9, pectoral-fin rays 17–21, caudal-fin rays 17, with 12–14 branched rays, pelvic-fins rays I, 5, lateral scales 28–32, transverse backward scales 8.5–10.5, predorsal scales 7–16, vertebrae 10+17=27.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED60977B229ECC5FE4E22414BDC" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0977B229ECC5FE4E22414BDC" blockId="35.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ECC5FE4E21684B85" bold="true" box="[199,355,402,428]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Distribution:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229ED6EFE4F22864B84" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1934" box="[364,653,403,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuiformis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ED6EFE4F22864B84" box="[364,653,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Glossogobius tenuiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known from its 
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF0977B229EFD4FE4F240D4B84" box="[982,1030,403,429]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E870FE4F24D24B84" box="[1138,1241,403,429]" name="Saint Lucia" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">St. Lucia</collectingCountry>
Lake, KwaZulu-Natal, localities along the South African coast from Mgeni River, Eastern Cape to KwaZulu Natal, and from Wadi Hasik and Wadi Shab, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229ED94FE0721D14BDC" box="[406,474,475,501]" name="Oman" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Oman</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="136911D80977B229EDE8FE0722364BDC" box="[490,573,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,747,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-70@34.[151,1436,747,1871]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 41. Distribution map of Glossogobius tenuiformis, Oman including two new locality records in the Wadis adjacent to the Arabian Sea coastal area. Pink: Southwestern Arabian Coast, green: Oman Mountains, and yellow: Arabian Interior." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541651" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541651/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED60977B229ECC5FE2321844E1C" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0977B229ECC5FE23237C4910" blockId="35.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ECC5FE2321364830" bold="true" box="[199,317,511,537]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229ED41FE2322E04830" authority="(Hamilton, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[323,747,511,537]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ED41FE2322284831" box="[323,547,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Glossogobius giuris</emphasis>
(Hamilton, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
was described from the Ganges River, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E89FFE2324DC4830" box="[1181,1239,511,537]" name="India" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">India</collectingCountry>
and is distributed in southern Red Sea; Indo-West Pacific: East Africa, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EEE2FDFF23334814" box="[736,824,547,573]" name="Yemen" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Socotra</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EF41FDFF23B54814" box="[835,958,547,573]" name="Seychelles" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EFC5FDFF24454814" box="[967,1102,547,573]" name="Madagascar" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and western Mascarenes, east to Society Islands, north to 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EDC9FD9B22474848" box="[459,588,583,609]" name="Philippines" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, south to Pilbara (
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF0977B229EF17FD9B23E9484B" box="[789,994,583,610]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF0977B229EFF7FD9B24724848" box="[1013,1145,583,609]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E88AFD9B24F9484B" box="[1160,1266,583,610]" name="Australia" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Australia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E932FD9B20E948AC" name="New Caledonia" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0977B229ECF2FDB721B648AC" author="Fricke, R. &amp; Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; Van der Laan, R." box="[240,445,619,645]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" refId="ref23694" refString="Fricke, R., Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; Van der Laan, R. (2022) Eschmeyer's Catalog of Fishes: Genera, Species, References. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp (accessed 20 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Fricke 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ED43FDB7217248AC" box="[321,377,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
). Based on uncertainty about the 
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF0977B229EF30FDB7236948AC" box="[818,866,619,645]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229EFE1FDB724CF48AD" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[995,1220,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229EFE1FDB724CF48AD" box="[995,1220,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Glossogobius giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its widespread distribution, a comprehensive study has been suggested to define the taxonomical status of this taxon. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0977B229E8FCFD5320E948E4" author="Hammer, M. P. &amp; Taillebois, L. &amp; King, A. J. &amp; Crook, D. A. &amp; Wedd, D. &amp; Adams, M. &amp; Bertozzi, T." pageId="35" pageNumber="486" pagination="87 - 100" refId="ref23923" refString="Hammer, M. P., Taillebois, L., King, A. J., Crook, D. A., Wedd, D., Adams, M. &amp; Bertozzi, T. (2021) Unravelling the taxonomy and identification of a problematic group of benthic fishes from tropical rivers (Gobiidae: Glossogobius). Journal of Fish Biology, 99 (1), 87 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 14701" type="journal article" year="2021">
Hammer 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229E967FD5325964880" box="[1381,1437,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
grouped the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229ED76FD6F21DC48E5" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[372,471,691,717]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ED76FD6F21DC48E5" box="[372,471,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">G. giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in four lineages based on molecular studies: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229E843FD6F248948E5" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1089,1154,691,716]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229E843FD6F248948E5" box="[1089,1154,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A” from 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E8E9FD6F254648E4" box="[1259,1357,691,717]" name="Vietnam" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E95AFD6F20D448D8" name="Bangladesh" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229ED16FD0B215148D8" box="[276,346,727,753]" name="China" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">China</collectingCountry>
; “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229ED73FD0B21B948D9" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[369,434,727,752]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ED73FD0B21B948D9" box="[369,434,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
B” from 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EE19FD0B22A248D8" box="[539,681,727,753]" name="South Africa" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EEDFFD0B231148D8" box="[733,794,727,753]" name="India" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">India</collectingCountry>
; “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229EF33FD0B237948D9" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[817,882,727,752]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229EF33FD0B237948D9" box="[817,882,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C” from 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EFD9FD0B241C48D8" box="[987,1047,727,753]" name="India" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E820FD0B249A48D8" box="[1058,1169,727,753]" name="Myanmar" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E899FD0B24EA48D8" box="[1179,1249,727,753]" name="Nepal" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229E8E9FD0B256548D8" box="[1259,1390,727,753]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EC95FD2720FD493C" box="[151,246,763,789]" name="Vietnam" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229ED34FD27217C493D" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[310,375,763,788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229ED34FD27217C493D" box="[310,375,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D” from 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EDDDFD27227B493C" box="[479,624,763,789]" name="South Africa" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. The 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0977B229EEA8FD2722E5493C" box="[682,750,763,789]" name="Oman" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Oman</collectingCountry>
populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229EF9BFD27243A493C" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1859" box="[921,1073,763,789]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229EF9BFD27243A493C" box="[921,1073,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Glossogobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is placed in the “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229E8ECFD272524493D" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1262,1327,763,788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229E8ECFD272524493D" box="[1262,1327,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D” group and it is now considered as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0977B229EDCFFCC323784910" authority="(Al Jufaili et al. 2022)" baseAuthorityName="Al Jufaili" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[461,883,799,825]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuiformis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229EDCFFCC322644910" box="[461,623,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">G. tenuiformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0977B229EE7FFCC323604910" author="Al Jufaili, S. M. &amp; Esmaeili, H. R." box="[637,875,799,825]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" refId="ref22187" refString="Al Jufaili, S. M. &amp; Esmaeili, H. R. (2022) Morphological analysis and DNA barcoding confirm presence of Sickle Pomfret, Taractichthys steindachneri (Doderlein, 1883) (Teleostei: Bramidae) in the Gulf of Oman. Zoology in the Middle East. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2022.2030531" type="book" year="2022">
Al Jufaili 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0977B229EEEDFCC3232C4910" box="[751,807,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
